bly needs another issue to discuss, but I would also like to have a simple way to silence or intercept logging (ideally without pulling in all of LoaderSupport?).\r\n\r\nIMO worker management should remain a case-by-case thing \u2014 my hunch is that loading glTF in a worker would actually introduce _more_ work on the main thread, because the glTF format is already heavily optimized for runtime parsing and what the worker serializes back may not be as optimal. Specific subtasks of the glTF loader (e.g. DRACO decompression) could certainly benefit from using a worker though.","created_at":"2017-11-16T19:55:00.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12615#issuecomment-345043712","id":345043712,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12615","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NTA0MzcxMg==","updated_at":"2017-11-16T19:55:00.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/345043712","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1848368?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/donmccurdy","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4NDgzNjg=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"donmccurdy","type":"User","id":1848368,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/orgs"}},{"index":13,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> @cnspaha there's an open suggestion here still: #12615 (comment)\r\n\r\nhaha yeah, that is the problem when working on multiple branches on multiple loaders :D \r\nsome things are getting overseen\/forgotten... \r\n\r\nadded commit with local variable","created_at":"2017-11-17T06:23:50.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12615#issuecomment-345156357","id":345156357,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12615","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NTE1NjM1Nw==","updated_at":"2017-11-17T06:23:50.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/345156357","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/22448974?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/cnspaha","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyNDQ4OTc0","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"cnspaha","type":"User","id":22448974,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/orgs"}},{"index":14,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"That does not solve the problem. The entire statement needs to be deleted otherwise you overwrite `this.path`. The actual problem with `TDSLoader` is that is does not pass the local `path`  variable of `.load()` as a parameter to the `.parse()` method. That's the way `GLTFLoader` and `ColladaLoader` work.","created_at":"2017-11-17T09:14:34.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12615#issuecomment-345187572","id":345187572,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12615","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NTE4NzU3Mg==","updated_at":"2017-11-17T09:14:50.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/345187572","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":15,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"The \"problem\" I currently seeing here is also that if we would pass the \"path\" to the parse function (which I would also recommend) that we would have to pass it down 4 function calls before it is needed again.  So readFile, readMeshData and readMaterialEntry would each need a \"path\" parameter and would just have to pass through it to the next function till readMap is reached. (see image)\r\n![image](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/22448974\/32945297-1f21672e-cb93-11e7-9e21-0a098f8b6709.png)\r\n\r\nSure it would be possible to just pass through the parameter but I don't really like this idea. \r\nusing `this.path` like it is currently is of course also out of the question.\r\n\r\nWhat do you think about adding a `this.currentPath` ? \r\nPer default it would be an empty string or undefined and instead of using a local `path` variable which we would have to pass through several functions (without doing anything there) we could later just access the `this.currentPath`. Of course the variable would be set back on each `.load`.  So it would be like a single-use (only for one file) path.\r\nDo you understand what I am trying to say?\r\n\r\n\r\nedit: I would also suggest to set the default value of `this.path` to `undefined`","created_at":"2017-11-17T11:35:43.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12615#issuecomment-345220892","id":345220892,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12615","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NTIyMDg5Mg==","updated_at":"2017-11-17T11:39:27.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/345220892","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/22448974?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/cnspaha","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyNDQ4OTc0","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"cnspaha","type":"User","id":22448974,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/cnspaha\/orgs"}},{"index":16,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I think the best solution is to re-write `TDSLoader` according to `GLTFLoader`. So the only public methods are `.load()`, `.parse()`, `.setCrossOrigin()` and `.setPath()`. All other code (which is related to parsing) should be encapsulated in separate functions. These functions could be nested inside the `.parse()` method (like `ColladaLoader`) or inside a top-level closure (like `GLTFLoader`). In this way, it's much easier to handle the mentioned scoping issue. And we would have a clean public interface of the loader.","created_at":"2017-11-17T13:42:42.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/12615#issuecomment-345246966","id":345246966,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12615","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NTI0Njk2Ng==","updated_at":"2017-11-17T13:42:42.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/345246966","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/org